Polish Central Banker is Against Too Many Rate Increases, Rp.pl Reports

-- B y   D o r o t a   B a r t y z e l
-- 
2011-05-19T05:06:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/polish-central-banker-is-against-too-many-rate-increases-rp-pl-reports.html
Polish central bank Governor Marek
Belka is against “too many” rate increases, he told Rp.pl in
an interview. The bank doesn’t raise rates “just in case,” but
only when it’s “inevitable,” he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dorota Bartyzel in Warsaw at 
 dbartyzel@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maciej Martewicz at 
 mmartewicz@bloomberg.net  